text.section:
Public employers, their representatives or their agents are prohibited from:
Interfering, restraining or coercing firefighters in the exercise of the rights guaranteed in KRS 345.030;
Dominating or interfering with the formation, existence or administration of any labor organization;
Discriminating in regard to hiring or tenure of employment or any term or condition of employment to encourage or discourage membership in any labor organization; provided, that nothing in this chapter, or in any other statute of this state, shall preclude a public employer from making an agreement with a labor organization to require as a condition of employment membership therein on or after the thirtieth day following the beginning of such employment or on the effective date of such agreement, whichever is the later;
Discharging or otherwise discriminating against an employee because he has signed or filed any affidavit, petition or complaint or given any information or testimony under this chapter;
Refusing to bargain collectively in good faith with a labor organization which is the exclusive representative of employees in an appropriate unit, including but not limited to the discussing of grievances with the exclusive representative.
